<br>
I made RR2 before hitting 30. It was hard, but I did it. Why? Because speed is speed. It may not have been the fastest thing out there, but I was willing to go out and do it. Was I a speed bump in the fight? Yes. I knew I would be. But you know, I wouldnt have done it any different. I still got invited into groups, and in RVR, that is all that matters (at least to me).<br>
<br>
The class has a few good features to it, speed being our most sought after item. Im a taxi cab. I accept that fact, and I live with it. If I didnt like it, I would play something else.<br>
<br>
Recently (that being within the last 3 months), I have noticed a marked difference in our survivablity. The 15 second timers did help alot. In RVR, I can now blast casters and healers a little more often, and usually at the right times. The slight bump in HP has actually been a boon for me. Sure, it can be taken out in one hit or spell, but its one more hit I can survive now.<br>
<br>
We have problems. I wont say our class is perfect. We arent on par with Minstrels or Bards. But you know, we arent exactly on par with any one class. We dont have a realm equivalent out there, if you think about it. We arent rogue based (thus eliminating Minsts and Bards). None of the other fighter based classes have the spec lines we do. So, we are a class unto ourselves. Unique, and only to Midgard. Its hard to really cry for balance when we are a class of our own. We have nothing to compare to.<br>
<br>
And with that in mind, for what we can do and what we have, I have to say that we are a solid class with some nagging issues. The pulse drops, the RA's. Those are our worst issues. Lets fix those before worrying about anything else right now.<br>
<br>
One thing at a time brings greater results in the long run than everything at once, which could end up being nerfed.<br>
<br>
(I know people may not agree with it, but I figure I would put my thoughts up anyway. I enjoy my skald, and prolly forever will. Im here for fun, not for the ub3r ph4t l00t or mega-RP's) <p>Bays Endruhms<br>
Skald of Ravensflyte<br>
Taxi-cab (Sojourner in training) of Midgard/Percival</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=clapperoth>Clapperoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/6/04 10:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=767.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Great Job!</span><hr size=1> Guys, can you take the name-calling and arguments about healers and minstrals to VN please?  This forum is to talk about skalds and skalds only.  When I see new posts here I keep checking them thinking there will be a useful discussion about skalds.<br>
